  "text": "Although obesity increases oxidative stress even during childhood, it is difficult to identify a typical oxidative stressrelated response, because most studies include different oxidative stress markers. ROS are produced during metabolic reactions, but it is largely unknown which factors modulate their production [CITATION_1] .",
